Uptrend Call Working As Mettler-Toledo Stock Rises 39.9% (MTD)



Written on Wed, 07/12/2017 - 1:41pm
 By Shiri Gupta
SmarTrend identified an Uptrend for Mettler-Toledo (NYSE:MTD) on November 8th, 2016 at $428.46.  In approximately 8 months, Mettler-Toledo has returned 39.88% as of today's recent price of $599.34.In the past 52 weeks, Mettler-Toledo share prices have been bracketed by a low of $343.61 and a high of $604.99 and are now at $599.34, 74% above that low price.  Over the last five market days, the 200-day moving average (MA) has remained constant while the 50-day MA has advanced 1.0%.Mettler-Toledo International Inc. manufactures and markets weighing instruments for use in laboratory, industrial, and food retailing applications. The Company also supplies several related analytical and measurement technologies. Mettler-Toledo provides its services to customers worldwide.SmarTrend will continue to scan these moving averages and a number of other proprietary indicators for any shifts in the trajectory of Mettler-Toledo shares.Log in and add Mettler-Toledo (MTD) to your watchlist today so you can receive a real-time alert when the shares are about to change trend.



